name: Park Case
about: Laptop provides serious performance for software development and machine learning. fingerprint sensor is not as responsive and usually takes a couple of tries to get it to work. Also, for a high end laptop, the webcam is comparatively of lower quality..

name: Conner Bowen
about: Machine runs great, love the 16:10 aspect ratio and it's crispy clear speakers. Though the battery lifespan could use some conservation, it doesn't take away the fact it's a powerful mobile workstation..

name: Terri Robles
about: Beautiful machine, it's replacing a long-in-the-tooth Thinkpad t450s (and a disappointing L580). Heft is about the same as the T450s, despite being a significantly larger screen..

name: Hillary Mcconnell
about: Light with generous screen space. Minimal screen glare. Very nice anti-smudge surface. Cool even with Xeon processor at high performance. Have to be mindful of battery life - with battery saver it is acceptable, might consider carrying a power brick on transatlantic flights..

name: Hutchinson Baxter
about: Love this! It's a perfect laptop for traveling to/from the office as it's light weight. Nice bright high resolution touch screen. Easy to connect my two monitors via dual HDMI connector..

name: Mckenzie Cooper
about: Got this to replace a Dell precision laptop. Have been with Dell since 1996 and have always upgraded to a Dell laptop since then. Bought the P1 after my current Dell less than a year old failed boot from a win10 to win11 forced upgrade by windows system. I am currently using it for software development and some video/photo editing and have had no issues so far. 16 inch screen laptop is same size if not a tad smaller than my 15.6 inch dell laptop which is a surprise to me.
